<DIV2 N="17" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>&para;How and after what &s;ort the Captaine Ge|nerall
was receiued in Calicut, &amp; how hee
tolde the king his me&s;&s;age which he carri|ed.
Cap. 17.</HEAD>
<P>_FRom this place he went forward on his
way, vntill &s;uch time he came to <HI>Calicut,</HI>
and at the entering of the &s;ame, they carri|ed
him w^t the re&s;t of his company to ano|ther
<HI>Pagode,</HI> lyke vnto that which he had
&s;&eacute;ene before, and when that he would haue
entered into the Citie, the people were &s;o many, as well of
tho&s;e that came forth of the &s;ame for to &s;&eacute;e our men, as al|&s;o
of tho&s;e that went with him, that for the multitude of
them, he could not goe in the &s;tr&eacute;ets, in&s;omuch that the Ge|nerall
meruailed to &s;&eacute;e &s;o many people: and when as h&eacute;e
&s;awe him&s;elfe to be there, he gaue God great thankes, for
