they are repo&s;ed in cities,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Why the chri&s;tians of y^e Indi|as hath a Pope.</NOTE> as is thought co~uenient. The cau&s;e
why they haue a pope in tho&s;e parts hath ben as is thought
by the~, for y^t in S. <HI>Peters</HI> time he being in <HI>Antioch,</HI> ther a|ro&s;e
a great &s;ci&s;me of <HI>Simon Magus,</HI> which was y^e occa&s;io~
y^<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter"> he was called to <HI>Rome</HI> to ouerthrow y^e &s;ame, &amp; to help y^e
chri&s;tians which wer in great trouble: and &s;&eacute;eing y^<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter"> he mu&s;t
depart fro~ <HI>Antioch,</HI> &amp; for y^t the church of y^<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter"> orient &s;huld not
remaine w^tout a &s;hepheard, he appointed a vicar to gouern,
